<p>I have many <strong>comboboxes</strong> with different <strong>DisplayMemberPathes</strong></p>  <p>I need create the one style with TextWrapping</p>  <p>App.xaml:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;Setter Property="ItemTemplate" &gt;               &lt;Setter.Value&gt;                  &lt;DataTemplate &gt;                 &lt;TextBlock Text="{Binding *what here?*}" TextWrapping="Wrap"/&gt;                 &lt;/DataTemplate&gt;          &lt;/Setter.Value&gt;      &lt;/Setter&gt; </code></pre>  <p>ComboBoxes:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;ComboBox DisplayMemberPath="val1" /&gt; &lt;ComboBox DisplayMemberPath="val2" /&gt; &lt;ComboBox DisplayMemberPath="val3" /&gt; </code></pre>  <p>So, I know, that I can create the property Value in each ComboBoxItem class and use it</p>  <pre><code> &lt;TextBlock Text="{Binding Value }" TextWrapping="Wrap"/&gt; </code></pre>  <p>But may be there is another way without create special property?</p>